.TH ESO-DOWNLOAD 1 "February 2026" "eso-download" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
eso-download \- Query and download data from the ESO Science Archive

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eso-download
.RI [ global-options ]
.B raw
.RI [ options ]

.br
.B eso-download
.RI [ global-options ]
.B phase3
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eso-download
is a command-line interface for querying and downloading data from the
ESO (European Southern Observatory) Science Archive.

It supports:

.TP
.B raw
Queries and downloads raw observational data.

.TP
.B phase3
Queries and downloads Phase 3 (processed, science-ready) data products.

The tool uses the astroquery ESO module and supports authenticated
access to proprietary data via the ESO User Portal.

.SH REQUIREMENTS
.IP \(bu 2
Python >= 3.10
.IP \(bu 2
astroquery >= 0.4.12.dev10525

.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B --user \fIUSERNAME\fR
ESO User Portal username. Enables authenticated queries.

.TP
.B --deauthenticate
Remove stored credentials for the given user from the keyring.

.TP
.B --max-rows \fIN\fR
Maximum number of records returned (default: 100).

.TP
.B --with-calib raw|processed
Download associated calibration files.

.TP
.B --count-only
Print number of matching records and exit.

.TP
.B --metadata-only
Write query results to CSV and exit without downloading data.

.TP
.B --outdir \fIDIR\fR
Output directory for downloaded files (default: eso_downloads).

.SH RAW OPTIONS
.TP
.B --run-id \fIID\fR
ESO Run ID (e.g. 090.C-0733(A)).

.TP
.B --instrument \fINAME\fR
Instrument name (e.g. FORS2).

.TP
.B --target-name \fINAME\fR
Target name substring match.

.TP
.B --ra \fIDEG\fR
Right Ascension in degrees.

.TP
.B --dec \fIDEG\fR
Declination in degrees.

.TP
.B --file-cat SCIENCE|CALIB|ACQUISITION
Filter by data product category.

.TP
.B --start-date YYYY-MM-DD
Start of observation date range.

.TP
.B --end-date YYYY-MM-DD
End of observation date range.

.SH PHASE3 OPTIONS
.TP
.B --proposal-id \fIID\fR
ESO Proposal ID (e.g. 094.B-0345(A)).

.TP
.B --collection \fINAME\fR
Survey/collection name (e.g. MUSE).

.TP
.B --instrument \fINAME\fR
Instrument name.

.TP
.B --facility \fINAME\fR
Facility name (e.g. ESO-VLT-U4).

.TP
.B --target-name \fINAME\fR
Target name substring match.

.TP
.B --ra \fIDEG\fR
Right Ascension in degrees.

.TP
.B --dec \fIDEG\fR
Declination in degrees.

.TP
.B --release-date-min YYYY-MM-DD
Release date range start.

.TP
.B --release-date-max YYYY-MM-DD
Release date range end.

.TP
.B --publication-date-min YYYY-MM-DD
Publication date range start.

.TP
.B --publication-date-max YYYY-MM-DD
Publication date range end.

.SH AUTHENTICATION
If
.B --user
is provided, the tool prompts for the ESO password and stores it securely
using the system keyring.

To remove stored credentials:

    eso-download raw --user USERNAME --deauthenticate

.SH OUTPUT
Query results are written to:

    query_results.csv

in the specified output directory.

Downloaded datasets are retrieved using astroquery and automatically
uncompressed.

.SH EXAMPLES

Count raw datasets:

    eso-download raw --run-id 090.C-0733(A) --count-only

Download Phase3 data by target:

    eso-download phase3 --target-name "NGC 253"

Query by sky position:

    eso-download raw --ra 129.0629 --dec -26.4093 --max-rows 20

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success.
Non-zero on authentication failure, version mismatch, or runtime errors.

